<Author>McDocEdmontonCanada
<Content>Excellent Hotel We stayed at this hotel for 3 nights in July 2008, with our two young-adult children in a family room for four. The location is excellent, on a fairly quiet street only a block from the subway. Many restaurants are nearby, and there are some excellent shops within easy walking distance. The hotel is old but in excellent repair, and refurbishing is underway with a new lift just installed. The breakfast was excellent and the staff were friendly and helpful. The only negative was lack of air conditioning in 31C weather, as our upper-floor room was very hot. Overall, an excellent choice for a visit to Berlin. 
