<Author>momskier
<Content>Location, Location, Location My daughter lives in Germany. We went to visit her recently and the 3 of us went to Berlin for a weekend. We are Choice Hotel members and used our points to stay at Comfort Hotel Auberge.We loved the hotel it was so centrally located. The hotel has a fabulous breakfast included in price of room. The room the 3 of us got was unbelieveable. There were 3 bedrooms, 2 baths, and a very nice living area. I'm guessing it was at one point a manager/owner apartment. We were able to park our car on the street with a special tag the hotel gave us for 5 E. I was expecting to pay more. The hotel is right next to the famous department store KaDeWe. KaDeWe is an experience not to be missed. The store was decorated for Xmas and just beautiful. The hotel was also near the metro at a major stop so very easy to get around. We took a sightseeing bus the first day to get aclimated to the city. Turned out to be a great idea. That was also right near hotel. If you are in Germany near XMAS don't miss the xmas markets in most cities. 
