<Author>TravellingCat
<Content>Great location for shopping I stayed here with my boyfriend 3 nights in December, 2005. We reserved double room through Internet and the reservation was ok. Room was large and spacious. I especially loved the high ceiling. Very simple equipments, there was only tv and couple of tables and beds, bathroom and safe. I think the rating was 3 stars. The hotel has no lift.Breakfast was free and there was plenty to choose from. Coffee especially was excellent! I think the best part was the location. Department store KaDeWe and the biggest shopping street was just right around the corner. Metro station was also very near.The staff was friendly and when we checked out, they let us storage our luggage there for a couple of hours. The lady at the reception was very friendly and she spoke very good english. They also call you a cab if you need one. This was appr. 110 euros per night, so it isn't the cheapest one, but if you plan to do some heavy shopping, then this hotel would be a very good choice. 
